<p>A broadcasted message is a message that is heard by everyone.
There is no general purpose broadcast protocol that anyone can use, possibly because it would be plagued by spam.
I have designed a broadcast protocol for a P2P network based on proof-of-work to minimize spam, called Proofnet.
<a href="https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=31038.0">See this post on the Bitcoin Forum for more information</a>.
</p>

